   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 05 · Continuum Removal & Bowl Occupancy\n",
    "\n",
    "Goal: demonstrate the *fingerprint scalar* used in the thesis (Figures 9–11). We rely on the \n",
    "packaged denoised spectra shipped with the repository and intentionally avoid re-running the \n",
    "Act-of-God denoiser."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Inputs\n",
    "- `data/reference/mamba_ssm/denoised_full_run.csv` — denoised relative reflectance for every \n",
    "  treatment/replicate.\n",
    "- `data/reference/reflectance/wavelength_grid.npy` — wavelength support (300–600 nm).\n",
    "\n",
    "Each spectrum already passed the readiness pipeline; we just replicate the continuum removal, \n",
    "quadratic bowl, and occupancy calculations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from __future__ import annotations\n",
    "\n",
    "import re\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n",
    "DENOISED_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / 'data' / 'reference' / 'mamba_ssm' / 'denoised_full_run.csv'\n",
    "WAVELENGTH_PATH = PROJECT_ROOT / 'data' / 'reference' / 'reflectance' / 'wavelength_grid.npy'\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', context='talk')\n",
    "\n",
    "DENOISED_PATH, WAVELENGTH_PATH"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "wavelengths = np.load(WAVELENGTH_PATH)\n",
    "denoised = pd.read_csv(DENOISED_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "wavelength_cols = [col for col in denoised.columns if col.startswith('reflectance_nm_')]\n",
    "numeric_wavelengths = np.array([float(col.split('_')[-1]) for col in wavelength_cols])\n",
    "numeric_wavelengths[:5], numeric_wavelengths[-5:]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Continuum Removal Helper\n",
    "\n",
    "Baseline subtraction locks the shoulders at the window bounds and subtracts the straight-line \n",
    "continuum, matching the approach used in Figures 9–10. We then fit an \"upside-down\" quadratic \n",
    "bowl with unit height (later scaled by the observed amplitude) and compute occupancy as the \n",
    "ratio of integrated signal to integrated bowl."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def continuum_removed(signal: np.ndarray, lam: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    lam_min, lam_max = lam[0], lam[-1]\n",
    "    y_min, y_max = signal[0], signal[-1]\n",
    "    baseline = y_min + (y_max - y_min) * (lam - lam_min) / (lam_max - lam_min)\n",
    "    cr = baseline - signal\n",
    "    return np.clip(cr, 0, None)\n",
    "\n",
    "def bowl_template(lam: np.ndarray, amplitude: float) -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    lam_min, lam_max = lam[0], lam[-1]\n",
    "    lam_center = 0.5 * (lam_min + lam_max)\n",
    "    halfwidth = 0.5 * (lam_max - lam_min)\n",
    "    lam_norm = (lam - lam_center) / halfwidth\n",
    "    bowl = amplitude * np.clip(1 - lam_norm**2, 0, None)\n",
    "    return bowl\n",
    "\n",
    "def occupancy_ratio(signal: np.ndarray, lam: np.ndarray) -> float:\n",
    "    cr = continuum_removed(signal, lam)\n",
    "    if cr.max() <= 0:\n",
    "        return 0.0\n",
    "    bowl = bowl_template(lam, cr.max())\n",
    "    numerator = np.trapz(cr, lam)\n",
    "    denominator = np.trapz(bowl, lam)\n",
    "    if denominator <= 0:\n",
    "        return 0.0\n",
    "    value = numerator / denominator\n",
    "    return float(np.clip(value, 0, 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "occupancy_ratio(np.array([1.0, 0.8, 0.6, 0.9, 1.0]), np.linspace(320, 480, 5))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Compute Occupancy per Spectrum\n",
    "\n",
    "We evaluate two windows: 320–480 nm (broad scytonemin bowl) and 360–410 nm (focused ROI)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "WINDOWS = {\n",
    "    'occ_320_480': (320.0, 480.0),\n",
    "    'occ_360_410': (360.0, 410.0),\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "def extract_window(row: pd.Series, lam_min: float, lam_max: float) -> tuple[np.ndarray, np.ndarray]:\n",
    "    mask = (numeric_wavelengths >= lam_min) & (numeric_wavelengths <= lam_max)\n",
    "    lam = numeric_wavelengths[mask]\n",
    "    signal = row[wavelength_cols].to_numpy()[mask]\n",
    "    return signal, lam\n",
    "\n",
    "def compute_occupancies(df: pd.DataFrame) -> pd.DataFrame:\n",
    "    result = df.copy()\n",
    "    for label, (lam_min, lam_max) in WINDOWS.items():\n",
    "        values = []\n",
    "        for _, row in df.iterrows():\n",
    "            signal, lam = extract_window(row, lam_min, lam_max)\n",
    "            values.append(occupancy_ratio(signal, lam))\n",
    "        result[label] = values\n",
    "    return result\n",
    "\n",
    "denoised_occ = compute_occupancies(denoised)\n",
    "denoised_occ[['relative_path', 'occ_320_480', 'occ_360_410']].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Σ Orientation Aggregator\n",
    "\n",
    "We aggregate across replicates/orientations (grouped by `group_id`) and then summarise by dose \n",
    "(treatment). This mirrors the Σ-occupancy narrative from Figure 11."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "group_occ = (\n",
    "    denoised_occ\n",
    "    .groupby('group_id')[['occ_320_480', 'occ_360_410']]\n",
    "    .mean()\n",
    "    .reset_index()\n",
    ")\n",
    "group_occ.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Dose ordering is encoded in the treatment label (`treatment_1`, `treatment_2`, …).\n",
    "We convert the suffix to integers for plotting."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
    "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def extract_dose(label: str) -> int:\n",
    "    match = re.search(r"treatment_(\\d+)", label)\n",
    "    return int(match.group(1)) if match else -1\n",
    "\n",
    "group_occ = group_occ.merge(\n",
    "    denoised_occ[['group_id', 'treatment']].drop_duplicates(),\n",
    "    on='group_id',\n",
    "    how='left'\n",
    ")\n",
    "group_occ['dose'] = group_occ['treatment'].map(extract_dose)\n",
    "group_occ.head()
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Acceptance Check: Σ-Occupancy vs Dose\n",
    "\n",
    "We expect Σ occupancy (320–480 nm) to peak at dose 2 then decline."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dose_summary = (\n",
    "    group_occ\n",
    "    .groupby('dose')[['occ_320_480', 'occ_360_410']]\n",
    "    .mean()\n",
    "    .reset_index()\n",
    "    .sort_values('dose')\n",
    ")\n",
    "dose_summary
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
    "plt.plot(dose_summary['dose'], dose_summary['occ_320_480'], marker='o', label='320–480 nm')\n",
    "plt.plot(dose_summary['dose'], dose_summary['occ_360_410'], marker='s', label='360–410 nm')\n",
    "plt.title('Σ Occupancy vs Dose')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Dose (treatment index)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Σ occupancy (mean across orientations)')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Interpretation\n",
    "- The broad bowl (320–480 nm) peaks near dose 2, then declines—matching Figure 11.\n",
    "- The tighter ROI (360–410 nm) trends similarly but with lower magnitude.\n",
    "- These scalars can be merged into `data/reflectance_canonical/` summaries or exported for \n",
    "  downstream regression."
   ]
  }
